ELIXIR FRONTMATTER — Standard Snippet
══════════════════════════════════════

All elixir-fenced code blocks in this system use the following
3-line frontmatter format. It is required on every file that
carries an imprint banner.

────────────────────────────────────────────────
FORMAT
────────────────────────────────────────────────

```elixir
/// status[STATUS] ver[MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH] created[YY.MM.DD]
/// doc[DOC_STATUS] modified[YY.MM.DD] auth[BASE]
/// Purpose or title of the file
```

────────────────────────────────────────────────
LINE MAP
────────────────────────────────────────────────

LINE 1 — Identity
  status    DRAFT | RESEARCH | ACTIVE | STABLE | ARCHIVED
  ver       Semantic version of the content
  created   Date first written (YY.MM.DD)

LINE 2 — Lifecycle
  doc       NONE | PARTIAL | COMPLETE
  modified  Date last changed (YY.MM.DD)
  auth      Originating base (ZEN.PRO | CITADEL | OBSIDIAN ...)

LINE 3 — Purpose
  Plain-text description of what this file is or does.

────────────────────────────────────────────────
RULES
────────────────────────────────────────────────

- status leads line 1 — it is what you check first.
- created trails line 1, modified trails line 2.
- auth updates with modified when a file changes base.
- No file path — the imprint banner carries identity.
- No authority/agent field — auth covers provenance.
- Bracket notation only: field[VALUE]. No colons, no pipes.

────────────────────────────────────────────────
EXAMPLE
────────────────────────────────────────────────

```elixir
/// status[RESEARCH] ver[1.0.0] created[25.12.14]
/// doc[COMPLETE] modified[26.03.02] auth[ZEN.PRO]
/// BEAM/OTP architecture vs alternatives for always-on agent systems
```

:: ∎
